@subutai - one example where it would be nice to have a type that matches the platform bitness is here:
https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/pull/343/files#diff-5fc4121d5c281de47186c9f30e425bdbR3782

The optimization wants to do arithmetic on a pointer so it needs a type that matches the platform.

The following macros are effective to resolve build errors.  However, I have not yet resolved testset errors.

```
--- a/python/sentencepiece.i
+++ b/python/sentencepiece.i
@@ -5,6 +5,10 @@
 
 %{
 #include <sentencepiece_processor.h>
+#if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x03000000
+#define PyString_AsStringAndSize(obj, s, len) {*s = PyUnicode_AsUTF8AndSize(obj, len);}
