@makdoudN no updates yet, for now it's possible to work around this by using a variable number of arguments in Python, e.g.,

```python
import ray

@ray.remote
class ParameterServer(object):
    pass

@ray.remote
class Worker(object):
    def __init__(self, *parameter_servers):
        self.parameter_servers = parameter_servers

ray.init()

parameter_servers = [ParameterServer.remote() for _ in range(4)]

worker = Worker.remote(*parameter_servers)
```

