Here's a "get started" script to reproduce it, given that your lambda file is called `lambda_dynamodb.js`:
```
zip lambda.zip lambda_dynamodb.js
awslocal dynamodb create-table \
         --attribute-definitions \
                AttributeName=id,AttributeType=S \
         --table-name local-test \
         --provisioned-throughput ReadCapacityUnits=1,WriteCapacityUnits=1 \
         --key-schema \
                AttributeName=id,KeyType=HASH
awslocal lambda create-function --function-name fdynamo --runtime=nodejs6.10 --role=r1 --handler=lambda_dynamodb.handler --zip-file fileb://lambda.zip
awslocal lambda invoke --function-name fdynamo result.log
```
